title: The manuscripts of His Grace the Duke of Portland, preserved at Welbeck abbey ...
snippet: Hence we went on to Plotterton, Lord Oxford's, Warton, cross the river to the Rye Hill up to ]\Iochill Toston, where at the house of one Carnaby, we refreshed ourselves with w^hat provision we had brought along with us, having been about six hours and three quarters on horseback, and rode about twenty miles.
